{
  "texts": [
    "The following is a brief introduction to the baseline models.Informer: Informer, proposed by [32], has mainly three innovative modules compared to the vanilla Transformer model and is designed for prediction of long sequences.",
    "The first innovative component is ProbSparse self-attention, which helps reduce time complexity and memory usage.",
    "The second innovative component is self-attention distilling, which trims the time dimension of inputs and helps receiving long sequence input.",
    "The third innovative module is called the generative style decoder, which combines historical data of a certain length with a predictive sequence filled with zeros as the input of the decoder.",
    "The informer model has been shown to be able to outperform the Transformer model [28,46]."
  ]
}